  "prompt": "Is muscle growth still possible after the age of 35?",
  "response": "Yes, muscle growth is still possible after the age of 35. While it may become more challenging due to factors such as natural decreases in hormone levels and slower recovery times, you can still achieve muscle growth with proper exercise, nutrition, and recovery strategies. Strength training exercises, adequate protein intake, and ensuring sufficient rest and recovery are key components for building muscle at any age. It is also important to consider personalized fitness plans and possibly consulting with a healthcare provider or fitness professional to design a program that suits your individual needs and goals.",
